organization.name: imls-gov

results.name: fy-2008-public-libraries-survey
results.notes:
Dig into FY 2008 data on public library systems (referred to as administrative entities in the Public Libraries Survey) and main libraries, branches, and bookmobiles (outlets in PLS). 

Use the administrative entity data to explore system-level organizational characteristics, staff, income and expenditures, sizes of collections, and library services offered to the public. Use the outlet-level data to find organizational characteristics such as public service hours and weeks open per year. 

Downloadable data files for the FY 2008 data collection are provided in comma separated value (.csv) and SAS (.sas7bdat) formats.
results.title: FY 2008 Public Libraries Survey

results.name: fy-2010-public-libraries-survey
results.notes:
Dig into FY 2010 data on public library systems (referred to as administrative entities in the Public Libraries Survey) and main libraries, branches, and bookmobiles (outlets in PLS). 

Use the administrative entity data to explore system-level organizational characteristics, staff, income and expenditures, sizes of collections, and library services offered to the public. Use the outlet-level data to find organizational characteristics such as public service hours and weeks open per year. 

Downloadable data files for the FY 2010 data collection are provided in comma separated value (.csv) and SAS (.sas7bdat) formats.
results.title: FY 2010 Public Libraries Survey

results.name: lsta-allotments-fy-2003-2016
results.notes:
Review Library Services and Technology Act (LSTA) allotments by state from FY 2003 to FY 2016.

The Grants to States program is the largest source of federal funding support for library services in the U.S. Using a population-based formula, more than $150 million is distributed among the state library agencies every year. 

Visit https://www.imls.gov/grants/grants-states to learn more about Grants to States.
results.title: LSTA Allotments (FY 2003-2016)
